FBIS3-23438 "jptot013__l94119" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 21 March 1994 WEST EUROPE CYPRUS Chairman of Solidarity Committee With Kurdistan Murdered Radio Gives Suspect's Description NC2103131094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1130 GMT 21 Mar 94 NC2103131094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] [passage omitted] The police announced that they are looking for a man of 30-35 who was seen leaving the scene at high speed aboard a small motorcycle of the Vespa type. According to the police announcement, this man is well built with short black hair and was wearing a dark sports jacket and dark trousers. [passage omitted] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said the police have information that yesterday afternoon, a foreign national was asking around the area near the Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation offices for information on the whereabouts of Thoukidhidhou Street, where the murdered man lived. The government spokesman also said that police will publish a sketch of the person within the day. [passage omitted] The government spokesman said Yeoryiadhis' murder is part of the Turkish secret services actions that aim to hurt the movement for Kurdistan. He also said it cannot be ruled out that another aim of the murder is to hurt the talks on the Cyprus issue. Responding to a question, Kasoulidhis said Yeoryiadhis' murder affects the climate of the talks. [passage omitted]
